"<p><strong>Address Parts</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>To better represent the complexity of addresses each constituent part has been modeled.</p>\n"
"\n"
"<p><strong>Building Name</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>Use to record the actual name of a Heritage Asset where known.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Street</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>Use to record the name of the street where the Heritage Asset is located.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Town or City</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>Use to record the name of the town or city where the Heritage Asset is located.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>County</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>Use to record the name of the county where the Heritage Asset is located.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Postcode</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>Use to record the postal code assigned to the Heritage Asset's location.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Townland</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>Use to record the name of the townland where the Heritage Asset is located.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Council</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>Use to record the name of the council responsible for the Heritage Asset.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Area Name</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>Use to record the name of the area where the Heritage Asset is located.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Area Type</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>Use to specify the type of area (e.g., district, barony) where the Heritage Asset is located.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Irish Grid Reference</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>Use to record the grid reference coordinates for the Heritage Asset's location using various formats, Alphanumeric TM65, Absolute TM65 or Long/Lat.</p>\n"
"<p><strong>Location Description</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>Use to provide a detailed description of the Heritage Asset's location. This can include landmarks, nearby intersections, or other notable features.</p>"
msgstr ""

#: cards:1
msgid ""
"<p><strong>Full Address</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>Where it is convenient, this can be used to record the full address. This can be used to aid migration from legacy systems with less sophisticated recording practice</p>\n"
"\n"
"<p><strong>Address Parts</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>To better represent the complexity of addresses each constituent part has been modelled.</p>\n"
"\n"
"<p><strong>Building Name</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>Use to record the actual name of a building where known.</p>\n"
"\n"
"<p><strong>Building Number</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>Use to record the number(s) assigned to a building. This may be a single number (eg. 45) or a range separated by a &#39;-&#39;&nbsp;(eg. 13-21).</p>\n"
"\n"
"<p><strong>Building Number Sub-Street</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n"
msgstr ""

